<div type="abstract"><head>Rat an Kunmunt von Giech</head><p>Der Rat teilt mit, dass König Sigismund kürzlich mit einigen Fürsten, Herren und Städten in Nürnberg einen Landfrieden beschlossen hat und der Adressat sich wegen Sicherheit an dessen Hauptmann wenden soll.</p>
</div>
<!--This div could possibly contain the analytic portion of the edition.-->
<div type="linguisticAnalysis"><ab><w join="" lemma="" msd="" part="" pos=""><fLib><f name=" "/></fLib></w></ab></div>
</front>
<body><div type="diplomatic"><pb facs="#facs_91" id="45v"/><!--The following div is the container for the adress lines of the letter.-->
<div type="addressee"><ab facs="#facs_91_r1l1">Dem veſten <expan>Kum<ex>m</ex>unt</expan> von Gych </ab>
</div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content"><ab facs="#facs_91_r1l2"><expan>Kümu<ex>n</ex>t</expan> von Gych als Jr vns <expan>verſchr<ex>iben</ex></expan> habt vvıe ewch dunk daʒ Jr <expan>vnſıch<ex>er</ex></expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_91_r1l3">vor vns vnd den <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex>n</expan> ſeyt etc das <expan>hab<ex>e</ex>n</expan> wır wol <expan>v<ex>er</ex>nom<ex>en</ex></expan> . vnd <expan>laſſ<ex>en</ex></expan> eẅch <expan>wıſſ<ex>en</ex></expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_91_r1l4">daʒ der <expan>all<ex>er</ex></expan> durchleẅchtıgſt fürſt vnd <expan>h<ex>er</ex>re</expan> . <expan>h<ex>e</ex>r</expan> <expan>Sıg<ex>mund</ex></expan> <expan>Römıſch<ex>er</ex></expan> vnd ʒu <expan>Vng<ex>er</ex>n</expan> etc </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_91_r1l5">künıg <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>gnedıgſt<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>h<ex>er</ex>re</expan> . als er nehſt hıe ʒu <expan>Nür<ex>emberg</ex></expan> <expan>geweſ<ex>en</ex></expan> ıſt / <expan>eın<ex>en</ex></expan> <expan>gemeine<ex>n</ex></expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_91_r1l6"><expan>Lantfr<ex>id</ex></expan> . <expan>ʒwıſch<ex>en</ex></expan> <expan>ettlıch<ex>en</ex></expan> . <expan>fürſt<ex>en</ex></expan> <expan>h<ex>er</ex>ren</expan> vnd <expan>Stett<ex>en</ex></expan> geſecʒt vnd gemacht hat </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_91_r1l7"><expan>darynne<ex>n</ex></expan> wır auch ſein / Denn dunkt eẅch daʒ Jr ʒu vns iht <expan>ʒuſpreche<ex>n</ex></expan> habt </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_91_r1l8"><expan>daru<ex>m</ex>b</expan> mugt Jr vns <expan>fürwende<ex>n</ex></expan> für den <expan>hawbtm<ex>an</ex></expan> vnd dıe bey Jm an <expan>demſelb<ex>e</ex>n</expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_91_r1l9"><expan>Lantfr<ex>id</ex></expan> <expan>ſıcʒe<ex>n</ex></expan> . VVas wır denn pıllıch <expan>od<ex>er</ex></expan> von rechts <expan>weg<ex>en</ex></expan> tun <expan>ſüll<ex>e</ex>n</expan> . das </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_91_r1l10"><expan>well<ex>e</ex>n</expan> wır tun . <expan>Dat<ex>um</ex></expan> vt <expan>ſ<ex>upra</ex></expan> </ab>
</div>
</div><div type="regularised"><pb facs="#facs_91" id="45v"/><!--The following div is the container for the adress lines of the letter.-->
<div type="addressee">
<ab>Dem vesten <expan>Kum<ex>m</ex>unt</expan> von Gych </ab>
</div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content">
<ab><expan>Kümu<ex>n</ex>t</expan> von Gych, als ir uns
                                <expan>verschr<ex>iben</ex></expan> habt, wie ewch dunk, daz ir
                                <expan>unsich<ex>er</ex></expan> vor uns und den
                                <expan>uns<ex>er</ex>n</expan> seyt etc., das
                            <expan>hab<ex>e</ex>n</expan> wir wol
                            <expan>v<ex>er</ex>nom<ex>en</ex></expan> und
                            <expan>lass<ex>en</ex></expan> ewch <expan>wiss<ex>en</ex></expan>, daz
                        der <expan>all<ex>er</ex></expan> durchlewchtigst fürst und
                                <expan>h<ex>er</ex>re</expan>
<expan>h<ex>e</ex>r</expan>
<expan>Sig<ex>mund,</ex></expan>
<expan>römisch<ex>er</ex></expan> und zu <expan>Ung<ex>er</ex>n</expan> etc.
                        künig, <expan>uns<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>gnedigst<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>h<ex>er</ex>re</expan>, als er nehst hie zu
                            <expan>Nür<ex>emberg</ex></expan>
<expan>gewes<ex>en</ex></expan> ist, <expan>ein<ex>en</ex></expan>
<expan>gemeine<ex>n</ex></expan>
<expan>lantfr<ex>id</ex></expan>
<expan>zwisch<ex>en</ex></expan>
<expan>ettlich<ex>en</ex></expan>
<expan>fürst<ex>en</ex></expan>, <expan>h<ex>er</ex>ren</expan> und
                                <expan>stett<ex>en</ex></expan> geseczt und gemacht hat,
                                <expan>darynne<ex>n</ex></expan> wir auch sein. Denn dunkt ewch, daz
                        ir zu uns iht <expan>zu spreche<ex>n</ex></expan> habt,
                                <expan>daru<ex>m</ex>b</expan> mugt ir uns
                            <expan>fürwende<ex>n</ex></expan> für den
                            <expan>hawbtm<ex>an</ex></expan> und die bey im an
                                <expan>demselb<ex>e</ex>n</expan>
<expan>lantfr<ex>id</ex></expan>
<expan>sicze<ex>n</ex></expan>. Was wir denn pillich
                            <expan>od<ex>er</ex></expan> von rechts <expan>weg<ex>en</ex></expan>
                        tun <expan>süll<ex>e</ex>n</expan>, das <expan>well<ex>e</ex>n</expan> wir
                        tun. <expan>Dat<ex>um</ex></expan> ut <expan>s<ex>upra</ex></expan>. </ab>
</div>
</div></body>
</text>
